Section 1: Q&A; Pairs

Example 1.1

User

What is a transformer model?
AI Response

A transformer is a deep learning architecture using self-attention mechanisms that process all tokens in
parallel, enabling efficient NLP. GPT and BERT are transformer-based models.

Example 1.2

User

What is reinforcement learning?
AI Response

Reinforcement learning trains an agent to make decisions by interacting with an environment and receiving
rewards or penalties, aiming to maximize cumulative reward over time.

Example 1.3

User

What is zero-shot learning?
AI Response

Zero-shot learning predicts unseen classes by leveraging semantic relationships or natural language task
descriptions, allowing LLMs to generalize without task-specific training.

Example 1.4

User

What is the softmax function?
AI Response

Softmax converts a vector of raw scores (logits) into probabilities that sum to 1, typically used as the final
activation in multi-class classification models.

Example 1.5

User

What is a decision tree?
AI Response

A decision tree splits data by feature values at internal nodes, with leaves representing predictions. They are
interpretable but prone to overfitting without pruning.

Example 1.6

User

What is RLHF?
AI Response

Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback trains a reward model on human preference data, then uses
RL (PPO) to fine-tune an LLM to produce outputs humans prefer.

Example 1.7

User

What is BERT?
AI Response



BERT (Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers) is a pre-trained transformer model that
understands context from both directions in a sentence, excelling at NLP classification tasks.

Example 1.8

User

What is feature engineering?
AI Response

Feature engineering creates or transforms input variables using domain knowledge to improve model
performance. It includes scaling, encoding, and creating interaction terms.

Example 1.9

User

What is machine learning?
AI Response

Machine learning is a branch of artificial intelligence that enables systems to learn and improve from
experience without being explicitly programmed.

Example 1.10

User

What is deep learning?
AI Response

Deep learning is a subset of machine learning that uses multi-layered neural networks to learn
representations of data. It excels at tasks like image recognition, NLP, and speech synthesis.



